<div class="question22"  style="display:none;">
<p class="question">
<h2><b><span style="color:red;">Test 6.22</span></b></h2>
 A 300 Hz sinusoid is sampled at 500 samples/s. The frequency of
  the sinusoid reconstructed from these samples is:

    <ul class="answers">
<img src="blank.png" width="15" id="q22ai"/><input type="radio" name="q22" value="a" id="q22a"><label for="q22a">0 Hz</label><br>       
<img src="blank.png" width="15" id="q22bi"/><input type="radio" name="q22" value="b" id="q22b"><label for="q22b">100 Hz</label><br>          
<img src="blank.png" width="15" id="q22ci"/><input type="radio" name="q22" value="c" id="q22c"><label for="q22c">200 Hz</label><br>        
<img src="blank.png" width="15" id="q22di"/><input type="radio" name="q22" value="d" id="q22d"><label for="q22d">300 Hz, obviously</label><br>
    </ul>
    
<script>
  document.getElementById('q22a').checked = false;
  document.getElementById('q22b').checked = false;
  document.getElementById('q22c').checked = false;
  document.getElementById('q22d').checked = false;
answer_value[22] = "c";
</script>
<div id="question22_answer" style="display:none;">
<span style="color:red;">Solution:</span><br>The sampled signal has components
at $\{\pm 300\pm 500k\}=\pm\{200,800,1200\dots\}$ Hz, for integers
$k$. The lowpass filter has a cutoff frequency at $\frac{500}{2}=250$ Hz,
leaving only 200 Hz.

</div>
<br>
</div>





<div class="question23"  style="display:none;">
<p class="question">
<h2><b><span style="color:red;">Test 6.23</span></b></h2>
Signal $x(t)=3\cos(2\pi 40t)+4\cos(2\pi 60t)$ is ideally sampled
  at 100 samples/s, then filtered by a brick-wall lowpass filter with
  a cutoff frequency of 50 Hz and a gain of 0.01:

$3\cos(2\pi 40t)+4\cos(2\pi 60t)\to$<div style="display: inline-block;border: 2px solid black;padding:2px;">100 samples/s</div>$\to$<div style="display: inline-block;border: 2px solid black;padding:2px;">
$\bf H (\omega)=\cases{.01, & $|\omega|<2\pi 50$\cr 0, & $|\omega|>2\pi
      50$}$</div>$\to y(t)$. What is the expression for $y(t)$?

    <ul class="answers">
<img src="blank.png" width="15" id="q23ai"/><input type="radio" name="q23" value="a" id="q23a"><label for="q23a">$y(t)=-\cos(2\pi 40t)$</label><br>       
<img src="blank.png" width="15" id="q23bi"/><input type="radio" name="q23" value="b" id="q23b"><label for="q23b">$y(t)=7\cos(2\pi 40t)$</label><br>          
<img src="blank.png" width="15" id="q23ci"/><input type="radio" name="q23" value="c" id="q23c"><label for="q23c">$y(t)=5\cos(2\pi 40t+53^\circ )$</label><br>        
<img src="blank.png" width="15" id="q23di"/><input type="radio" name="q23" value="d" id="q23d"><label for="q23d">$y(t)=5\cos(2\pi 40t-53^\circ )$</label><br>
    </ul>
    
<script>
  document.getElementById('q23a').checked = false;
  document.getElementById('q23b').checked = false;
  document.getElementById('q23c').checked = false;
  document.getElementById('q23d').checked = false;
answer_value[23] = "b";
</script>
<div id="question23_answer" style="display:none;">
<span style="color:red;">Solution:</span><br>$4\cos(2\pi 60t)$ aliases to
$4\cos(2\pi 40t)$ and adds to $3\cos(2\pi 40t)$, giving $7\cos(2\pi
40t)$.

</div>
<br>
</div>





<div class="question24"  style="display:none;">
<p class="question">
<h2><b><span style="color:red;">Test 6.24</span></b></h2>
The spectrum of a trumpet playing note A has a fundamental of 440 Hz
  and all harmonics above the tenth are negligible. The Nyquist
  frequency is:
    <ul class="answers">
<img src="blank.png" width="15" id="q24ai"/><input type="radio" name="q24" value="a" id="q24a"><label for="q24a">2.2 kHz</label><br>       
<img src="blank.png" width="15" id="q24bi"/><input type="radio" name="q24" value="b" id="q24b"><label for="q24b">4.4 kHz</label><br>          
<img src="blank.png" width="15" id="q24ci"/><input type="radio" name="q24" value="c" id="q24c"><label for="q24c">8.8 kHz</label><br>        
<img src="blank.png" width="15" id="q24di"/><input type="radio" name="q24" value="d" id="q24d"><label for="q24d">17.6 kHz</label><br>
    </ul>
    
<script>
  document.getElementById('q24a').checked = false;
  document.getElementById('q24b').checked = false;
  document.getElementById('q24c').checked = false;
  document.getElementById('q24d').checked = false;
answer_value[24] = "c";
</script>
<div id="question24_answer" style="display:none;">
